<HEADLINE> Sichuan Province Donates Cash To Tibet Snowstorm Relief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, January 15 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Sichuan
Province has donated one million yuan to the northern part of the
Tibet Autonomous Region, which has suffered under heavy snowfalls
since September.
</P>
<P>
A ceremony was held in Chengdu, the provincial capital, today
to mark the event.
</P>
<P>
Snowstorms have threatened the lives of Tibetans living in
Nagqu and Ari prefectures and their livestock. 
</P>
