<HEADLINE> Large Auto Group Established by China's Aviation Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 15 (Xinhua) -- China's aviation sector today
set up a group to produce more than a fourth of the country's vans.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhu Yuli, president of the Aviation Industries of
China (AVIC), the AVIC Van (Group) Corp. has an annual production
capacity of 120,000 vans, and the figure will increase to 300,000
in the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The group consists of the Harbin Aircraft Industry Corp., the
Guizhou Aviation Industry Group, the Changhe Aviation Industry
Corp., and the Harbin Dong'an Engine Corp., all of which are major
aviation businesses that manufacture aircraft parts and vans.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the group aims to improve the aviation
industry's structure and help the aviation industry turn military
production into civilian production, and promoting vans, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
The new group has 5.3 billion yuan in assets capital and 2.1
billion yuan in registered capital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
