<HEADLINE> Viag Earnings Up Sharply in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 15 (Xinhua) -- Germany's energy and utilities
conglomerate Viag registered double-digit growth in profits in
1997, the group's chief executive Georg Obermeier said Wednesday
night in Duesseldorf.
</P>
<P>
Obermeier did not specify the profit figures in his remarks to
be released today. Viag's pre-tax profits were 2.3 billion marks
(1.3 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
According to him, Viag's turnover last year reached almost 50
billion marks, compared with 42.5 billion in 1996. For 1998, the
company expected to gain at least 10 percent in its turnover.
</P>
<P>
The Viag boss added that the company was considering raising
dividend payout and offering a bonus to mark Viag's 75th
anniversary. 
</P>
</TEXT>
