<HEADLINE> Book On Jail Studies Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 15 (Xinhua) -- The 'General Studies on Jails',
a book about China's prison system, was released today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The book is the first to appear since the People's Republic of
China was founded in 1949. It discusses China's experience with
prison management, according to Jin Jian, president of the China
Association of Jail Researchers.
</P>
<P>
According to Li Kangtai, a professor from People's University
of China, China has a prison system with Chinese characteristics
that has proven to work.
</P>
<P>
A study last November showed about 1.43 million prisoners in
China, and a recidivism rate below 8 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
