<HEADLINE> Greater Efforts Called for Cultural, Ethical Progress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 15 (Xinhua) -- Wei Jianxing, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party
of China Central Committee, told a national meeting on cultural
and ethical progress today that there must be continued efforts in
cultural and ethical work.
</P>
<P>
Even though a good job is done in economic work, Wei said, the
whole Party must attach greater importance on advancing cultural
and ethical progress to use the initiative and creativity of the
general public.
</P>
<P>
The 15th Party National Congress' theme of holding the great
banner of the Deng Xiaoping Theory high, emancipating the mind,
and seeking truth from facts must be kept in mind, he said,
outlining three needs in building cultural and ethical
progress: Persisting in using Deng Xiaoping Theory as a guiding
principle; persisting in making economic construction the central
task; and persisting in being oriented toward the masses.
</P>
<P>
He also called for measures to increase the Party's role in
cultural and ethical progress, and urged Party officials to
increase their sense of responsibility and urgency and to do a
good job in this. 
</P>
</TEXT>
