<DOCNO> XIE19980116.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Defines Position on Internet Telephony </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 15 (Xinhua) -- Those hooked to PC's chatting
away via Internet telephony will continue to enjoy their almost
free long distance calls over mike and loudspeaker in European
Union countries.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission, the executive body of the 15-nation
union, defined Thursday its position toward Internet telephony in
the context of the liberalization of the union's
telecommunications market.
</P>
<P>
Under the defined EU law, the provision of voice service on the
Internet is not voice telephony and may therefore not be subject
by member states to individual licensing procedures.
</P>
<P>
Voice communications can be made through the commercial
services provided either from PC to PC, between PC and telephone
handsets connected to the public switched telecommunications
network (PSTN), or between two telephone handsets connected to
PSTN.
</P>
<P>
Only the third and last way is currently regarded as being
close to voice telephony or voice communications.
</P>
<P>
Internet telephony can be defined as voice telephony and
therefore be subject to standard voice telephony regulation only
if the communications are the subject of a commercial offer; the
service is provided for the public; the service is provided to and
from PSTN, and the service involves direct transport and speech in
real time.
</P>
<P>
The commission considered that Internet telephony currently
does not meet all these criteria and therefore will not be
considered as voice telephony for the time being.
</P>
<P>
The commission's definition will keep markets open for
innovation regarding the Internet, which could lead to multimedia
telephony offered over the computer network.
</P>
<P>
Voice on the Internet will therefore still enlarge the scope of
services available to consumers and is likely to help foster
consumer access to what is commonly known as the Information
Society.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980116.0017 </DOCNO>
