<HEADLINE> France Hails Mission to Algeria by EU Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 15 (Xinhua) -- France Thursday hailed the
confirmation by the European Union (EU) and Algeria that a EU
ministerial delegation will visit Algeria to discuss ways to stop
the massacre of civilians by Islamic militants in the country.
</P>
<P>
French Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret said
France was delighted by the EU's plan to send a ``mission of
listening and dialogue with the Algerian authorities in all its
components,'' next week.
</P>
<P>
The mission will consist of ministerial level officials from
Britain, Luxembourg and Austria, which are the present, preceding
and the next presidency states of the EU, also called EU Troika.
</P>
<P>
``France hopes the dialogue between the European Union and
Algeria can be pursued and deepened. We are delighted with this
news,'' said the spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
The British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook and the Algerian
Foreign Minister Ahmed Attaf both confirmed Thursday the EU Troika
mission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
