<HEADLINE> Italy, China Maintain Global Multipolarization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 15 (Xinhua) -- Italian President Oscar Luigi
Scalfaro told visiting Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen here
Thursday that the world should be multi-polarized and China will
play a significant role in the process of global multi-polarization.
</P>
<P>
No political or economic sector consensus should be imposed on
another country, since each country in the world has its own
situation, said Scalfaro.
</P>
<P>
Qian, also foreign minister of China, backed Scalfaro's view,
saying that world stability cannot be based on either a single
pillar or the past two confronting pillars.
</P>
<P>
Qian arrived here Wednesday for a four-day official visit to
Italy and San Marino following his visit to Morocco, Algeria and
Malta. 
</P>
</TEXT>
