<HEADLINE> German FM Expresses Confidence in Eastern Slavonia's Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 15 (Xinhua) -- German Foreign Minister Klaus
Kinkel Thursday expressed confidence in the future of Eastern
Slavonia which is being returned to Croatia following two years of
United Nations administration.
</P>
<P>
"I'm confident that the Croatian government and Serb
representatives in the region have the genuine will to continue
the course towards reconciliation even after the end of the UN
mandate," Kinkel said.
</P>
<P>
Germany, which has been supporting Eastern Slavonia's
reintegration into Croatia from the start, will continue to offer
assistance to the reconciliation process there, he added.
</P>
<P>
The UN took control of Eastern Slavonia in January 1996 from
the Serb forces that seized it in 1991. At midnight Thursday the
UN mandate will officially expire and Croatia will finally have
full control of all the land within its borders. 
</P>
