<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Should Not Ban Canadian Beef, WTO Rules </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, January 15 (Xinhua) -- The World Trade Organization
(WTO) has ruled that the European Union is breaking international
trading rules by banning Canadian hormone-treated beef, said
reports today.
</P>
<P>
Canadian sources said that Ottawa has received the confidential
ruling from the WTO, but will not make any comment until the
decision becomes public Friday.
</P>
<P>
Since 1989, Canada has not been able to export beef to the
lucrative European market.
</P>
<P>
A favorable ruling could open the market up again, Vern
Greenshields, spokesman for the Canadian Agriculture Ministry, was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The WTO ruled in favor of Canadian challenges to the EU beef
ban last summer.
</P>
<P>
The EU appealed, arguing that beef treated with growth hormones
was unhealthy.
</P>
<P>
The WTO appeals body ruled that the EU failed to provide an
assessment of the health risk that justified the ban. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
