<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 15 (Xinhua) -- Britain, the current European
Union (EU) president, announced here this afternoon that the EU
delegation will leave for Algeria on 19 January.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the 15-nation bloc, the British Foreign Office
said in a statement, "The (EU) presidency and the Algerian
government have agreed that the EU Troika mission will visit
Algeria on 19-20 January."
</P>
