<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-15 17:28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iraqi Foreign Minister to Visit Iran Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 15 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi Foreign Minister Mohammed
Saeed al-Sahhaf is expected to arrive here Friday for an official
visit, Iran's official news agency IRNA reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
IRNA quoted an unnamed official from the Iranian Foreign
Ministry as saying that Sahhaf's visit will focus on the
outstanding issues between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
However, a Western diplomat here said that Sahhaf will try to
win Tehran's support for Baghdad to break Western isolation,
particularly to solve the current crisis over arms inspection.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has been blocking a U.N. arms inspection team led by
American Scott Ritter, whom it accused as a U.S. spy, from
carrying out search for weapons of mass destruction because of the
"unbalanced" composition of the team.
</P>
<P>
Speaker of the Iraqi Parliament Saadoun Hammadi has forwarded a
letter to Iranian President Mohammad Khatami, asking Iran, now
chairman of the Organization of the Islamic Conference, to help
lift the U.N. sanctions imposed on Iraq since its invasion of
Kuwait in 1990.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that Sahhaf also will discuss the issue of
prisoners of war (POW) and payment of war reparations between the
two countries in order to improve relations between the two former
enemies.
</P>
<P>
Iran and Iraq fought an eight-year bloody war in 1980-88 which
killed hundreds of thousands of Iranian and Iraqi soldiers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
