<HEADLINE> Commonwealth Chief Voices Concern Over Vanuatu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 15 (Xinhua) -- Secretary-General Chief of
the Commonwealth Emeka Anyaok voiced concern here today over the
domestic violence in the South Pacific nation of Vanuatu.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the Vanuatu authorities have declared a
two-week state of emergency following rampant riots in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The London-based Commonwealth secretariat said in a statement
that the secretary-general chief had expressed concern about
violence in the capital Port Vila and called on all sides
concerned to remain calm.
</P>
<P>
"He (Anyaok) expressed the hope that all parties would work
together to resolve their problems for the good of the nation,"
the statement said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
