<HEADLINE> UK to Transfer 7 IRA Prisoners to Ireland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 15 (Xinhua) -- The Irish government announced
in Dublin today that Britain would transfer seven Irish Republican
Army (IRA) prisoners to Ireland to serve the rest of their
sentences.
</P>
<P>
An Irish Justice Department spokesman was quoted by press
reports from Dublin as saying today, "We've had two or three
prisoner transfers in the last couple of years but this is the
biggest group ever."
</P>
<P>
The spokesman noted that the seven IRA men, five of whom were
sentenced in 1997 to 35-year imprisonment, would be moved to the
high-security Portlaoise prison 50 miles (80 km) from Dublin.
</P>
<P>
Political commentators said that the move was the latest effort
to give an impetus to the Northern Ireland peace process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
