<HEADLINE> Rwanda Launches Private Airline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 15 (Xinhua) -- The launching of Rwanda
Airlines company marked a great leap forward in breaking the
country's isolation, said the manager of the new company here
today.
</P>
<P>
Rwandan businessman, Charles Ngarambe, who is running the
company, was quoted by the Rwandan News Agency as saying that he
established the airlines because he knew Rwanda is landlocked and
has no easy air links with outside.
</P>
<P>
"I'll put it at the disposal of Rwandans for charter" he
underlined, adding that he would even undercut other airlines
operating in the region.
</P>
<P>
Rwanda Airlines, with its "mountain gorilla in the sunset"
logo, is opened by Ngarambe, a reknown Rwandan businessman, after
the merger of state-owned Air Rwanda and the South African
Alliance Airlines.
</P>
<P>
At present, this company has a BAC 1-ll 78-seat jet which
Ngarambe said is second-hand, but still in excellent condition.
</P>
<P>
However, Rwanda Airlines faces a tough competition with other
regional airlines like Cameroun Airlines, Uganda Airlines, and
kenya Airways which are on the regional routes.
</P>
<P>
No definite routes for Rwanda Airlines have been so far fixed
for Rwanda Airlines, but it is scheduled to link Rwanda to
various cities of the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
