broadcasts daily in four languages, Amhara, Oromo, Tigray and
English. Voice of Ethiopia, run by the Ethiopian government, and
Radio Fana, run by the ruling Ethiopian People's Revolutionary
Democratic Front, are two radio stations in Ethiopia. 
