<HEADLINE> Russia, Turkmenistan Reach Agreement on Gas Purchases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 15 (Xinhua) -- Moscow and Ashgabat have reached
in principle an agreement on purchases of Turkmen gas, the
Interfax news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to Gazprom Chief Executive Rem Vyakhirev, who paid a
visit to Ashgabat Wednesday, Gazprom, Russia's gas giant, would
purchase the gas itself without any intermediaries.
</P>
<P>
He said Gazprom was ready to purchase about 30 billion cubic
meters of gas in Turkmenistan, but considered the proposed price
of 42 U.S. dollars for 1,000 cubic meters on the Central Asian
market was too high.
</P>
<P>
Vyakhirev believed that there were a number of actors that went
into pricing the gas. He warned that it would be difficult to find
buyers for that amount of gas in Russia, the Commonwealth of
Independent States (CIS), and Eastern Europe who were ready to pay
cash.
</P>
<P>
He said that any purchase agreement could be realized only when
all pricing issues were resolved.
</P>
<P>
It was said that both sides had set up working groups to
consider the issue. The groups might meet in Moscow on January 26.
</P>
</TEXT>
