<HEADLINE> Greek Seamen Striking over Cabotage Restrictions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, January 15 (Xinhua) -- Greek seamen staged a nationwide
strike on Thursday in protest against the lifting of cabotage
coastal shipping restrictions under European Union (EU) transport
deregulations.
</P>
<P>
The seamen's 24-hour strike brought the country's shipping
transport to a standstill as all Greek-flag merchant vessels
anchored at ports, the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA)
reported.
</P>
<P>
The cabotage restrictions ceases to be in effect for
cruiseships as of 1999 and for coastal shipping as of 2004. Under
which, only Greek vessels are allowed to carry out coastal
passenger and cargo routes originating in one Greek port and
ending in another Greek port.
</P>
<P>
Yannis Halas, secretary general of the Hellenic Seamen's
Federation (PNO), said today that the scrapping of the
restrictions would create severe unemployment problems among the
Greek seamen. 
</P>
