<HEADLINE> Pirated Audio and Video Products Destroyed In Southern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 16 (Xinhua) -- At least a million pirated
audio and video products were crushed this morning in Guangzhou,
the capital of south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Provincial Vice-governor Li Lanfang said that the government of
Guangdong has paid a great deal of attention to protecting
intellectual property rights and cracking down on pirated and
pornographic products.
</P>
<P>
Since the winter of 1996, more than seven million illegal audio
and video products have been confiscated and over 30 large places
dealing in illegal products closed down.
</P>
<P>
In addition, more than 40 underground VCD production lines were
discovered with the help of local people who have been active in
providing information about acts of piracy.
</P>
<P>
The vice-governor said that the province will continue its
fight against piracy to give China a better image in the world in
protecting intellectual property rights. 
