<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980116.0083 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stocks Rise Sharply in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Tokyo stock prices rose sharply
Friday on optimism for additional economic measures fueled by
Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto's remark suggesting extra steps
to stabilize the financial system and revitalize the economy.
</P>
<P>
The key Nikkei index recovered the 16,000 line for the first
time since December 18.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei average of 225 selected issues on the First Section
at the Tokyo Stock Exchange jumped 924.47 points or 6.11 percent
from Wednesday's close to 16,046.45.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
issues on the First Section, surged 52.60 points or 4.5 percent to
1,201.71.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the First Section came to an estimated 700 million
shares, up from Wednesday's 409.48 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Nippon Steel was Friday's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
Hashimoto's comment in the early afternoon that he will do his
best to restore confidence in the financial system and revitalize
the economy fueled the upturn. 
</P>
</TEXT>
