<DOCNO> XIE19980116.0087 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-16 15:42 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey's Pro-Islamic Party RP Shut Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 16 (Xinhua) -- President of Turkey's
Constitutional Court Ahmet Necdet Sezer Friday announced the
closure of Turkey's pro-Islamic Welfare Party (RP) headed by
former Prime Minister Necmettin Erbakan.
</P>
<P>
Sezer made the announcement following the voting of the members
of the Constitutional Court on the ban with nine for and two
against, which started at 14:30 local time (12:30 GMT).
</P>
<P>
Under the decision, the status of Erbakan's deputy and other
five RP deputies in the parliament would be canceled when the
Turkish Official Gazette is published, said Sezer.
</P>
<P>
The case, demanding the Islamist party be shut down on the
grounds of its support for fundamentalism, was filed by Turkey's
High Appeals Court Chief Prosecutor Vural Savas with the
Constitutional Court last May.
</P>
<P>
Security was tightened around the building of the
Constitutional Court during the meeting on the closure of the RP.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of reporters and correspondents waited outside the
building for the verdict.
</P>
<P>
According to Turkey's Party Law, Erbakan and some senior RP
officials will be banned from engaging in politics for at least
five years if the party is outlawed.
</P>
<P>
Erbakan, 71, resigned as prime minister last June under
pressure from the pro-secular military which criticized him for
his reluctance to take tough measures against fundamentalism.
</P>
<P>
Erbakan's political career started in 1967. He became the
chairman of the National Order Party. After the closure of this
party by the Constitutional Court, Erbakan went abroad and stayed
out of politics for a while.
</P>
<P>
He returned to Turkey and continued his political career with
the National Salvation Party. This party was banned again during
the the military coup on September 12, 1980 and Erbakan was
imprisoned in a military jail for a few years.
</P>
<P>
Following his release, Erbakan joined the RP, which was
founded on July 19, 1983, and became the leader of the party in
1987. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
