<HEADLINE> China Plans To Improve Disaster Readiness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, January 16 (Xinhua) -- China has greatly improved its
ability to deal with natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
Last year alone, the country's flood combatting efforts helped
cut losses by some 150 billion yuan, meaning an increase of 180
yuan per capita in income for rural people, according to a
national conference on water resources in session in this capital
of Hainan Province.
</P>
<P>
The country also saved over 59 billion kilograms of grain from
drought damage, equal to nearly 12 percent of the total grain
output of the year.
</P>
<P>
Floods last year affected 1.1 million hectares of crops and
drought affected another 3.3 million hectares. 
</P>
