<HEADLINE> Maier Wins World Cup Downhill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Austrian Hermann Maier claimed
his fifth successive World Cup title after winning the downhill
event in Wengen, Switzerland, on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Austrian clocked one minute 44.89 seconds, the first win
for the Austrians in the Swiss resort since 1985.
</P>
<P>
Frenchman Nicolas Burtin finished second in 1:45.57 and Maier's
compatriot Andreas Schifferer was third in 1:45.61.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old Maier made light of clipping a gate on his way
down in a race reduced in distance because of the misty conditions.
</P>
<P>
Maier, a former bricklayer and ski instructor, leads the
overall World Cup standings and looks assured of giving Austria
their first win in that category in the 1990's. 
</P>
