<HEADLINE> Chinese Culture Minister Says Last Year Was Big Year For Culture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Minister of Culture Liu Zhongde
told the ministry's annual meeting today that 1997 was a
historical year for culture and arts in China and that artists
held the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory high.
</P>
<P>
Advances were made in reforming state-owned theatrical troupes,
which were badly influenced by Soviet methods and sluggish.
</P>
<P>
There were more artistic performances last year like the
country's fifth art festival, he said, and the climax was an
evening performance to celebrate the return of Hong Kong to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
He also said that China investigated a certain amount of
illegal activities in the sector, and that vulgar performances and
beauty contests have been curbed, but that highbrow arts,
traditional arts, and healthy pop arts are going through a good
period.
</P>
<P>
He praised cultural exchanges with foreign countries and the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, Taiwan, and Macao, and
the effort to limit decadent foreign culture.
</P>
<P>
The major problems are a shortage of funds and a lack of very
good artistic works, the minister concluded. 
