JOHANNESBURG, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Three people were killed
and 30 others injured when a bus overturned this morning in South
Africa's Kwazulu-Natal Province, South African Press Association
reported.
</P>
<P>
The bus overturned and crashed into an embankment between
Ixopo and Umzinto southwest of Durban after the driver apparently
lost control in a curve.
</P>
<P>
Two men and a woman died during the accident.
</P>
<P>
A local traffic official said, the driver, who was also
injured, was in a state of shock and couldn't explain what
happened. 
</P>
