<HEADLINE> HK Court Insolvency Cases Total 1,142 in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 16 (Xinhua) -- The total number of new court
insolvency cases hit 1,142 in 1997, 42 more than that of 1996,
Hong Kong's Official Receiver Robin Hearder said Friday.
</P>
<P>
But "it was still low in comparison with other overseas
jurisdictions in view of the high volume of economic activity in
Hong Kong," Hearder commented.
</P>
<P>
Of the new court insolvency cases, there were 503 new
compulsory liquidations of companies and 639 new bankruptcies.
</P>
<P>
The number of new compulsory liquidations was about 0.1 percent
of the total number of companies, or 1 percent of the number of
new companies incorporated during the year, he added.
</P>
<P>
The nature of the businesses which were the subject of
compulsory liquidation and bankruptcy included garment, knitting
and textile manufacturing, restaurant and canteen, import and
export as well as construction and engineering. 
</P>
</TEXT>
