<HEADLINE> Sustainable Development Put in First Place: HK Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Sustainable development will
be placed firmly in the center of government policy formulation
and strategic planning, a Hong Kong official said Friday.
</P>
<P>
It will also form the central theme of a new White Paper on the
Environment to be published in 2000, said Deputy Secretary for
Planning, Environment and Lands Benjamin Tang.
</P>
<P>
He told government green managers at the second Green Manager
Plenum that the government is committed to ensuring that Hong Kong
becomes a world class city and acknowledges that this requires a
first class environment.
</P>
<P>
"To achieve this objective, we need to do more than we have
been able to so far and strike a better balance amongst economic
and social development and the environment," said Tang.
</P>
<P>
It means that each and every bureau and department of the
government will have a much greater responsibility for
environmental concerns, he added.
</P>
<P>
The green managers were updated on recent developments in
environmental protection and green management: the trial on the
use of liquefied petroleum gas for taxis, the signing of a new
agreement with Canada on environmental cooperation, and the
stepped-up cooperation with neighboring Guangdong province in the
field. 
</P>
</TEXT>
