<HEADLINE> Soeharto, Mahathir to Discuss Regional Economic Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad is scheduled to arrive here Saturday morning to
meet with President Soeharto and discuss the regional economic and
financial crisis, a senior official said Friday.
</P>
<P>
"I think the reason for the Malaysian prime minister's visit is
the same as the recent visit of Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chock
Tong. They will discuss the monetary crisis in our region,"
Minister/State Secretary Moerdiono said.
</P>
<P>
Moerdiono also said that on Thursday night, at about 23:00
local time, President Soeharto spoke by phone with U.S. President
Bill Clinton.
</P>
