Clinton and the American people for their attention to Indonesia
in overcoming the monetary crisis," Moerdiono said.
</P>
<P>
Clinton said he was pleased with the results of talks between
Soeharto and IMF (International Monetary Fund) Managing Director
Michel Camdessus.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia, like other Southeast Asian countries, has been badly
hit by the current monetary crisis. The rupiah has lost more than
200 percent of its value against the US dollar since July last
year.
</P>
<P>
In October last year, Indonesia agreed to an IMF-led 23 billion
dollars bailout package. In exchange, Indonesia vowed to dismantle
trading monopoly, overhaul the financial sector and scrap or
suspend costly infrastructure projects.  
