<HEADLINE> Northwest China Region Reports Foreign Trade Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, January 16 (Xinhua) -- The Ningxia Hui Autonomous
Region in northwest China had reported some 300 million US dollars
in imports and exports in 1997, a record increase of 25.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Imports were valued at 51 million US dollars, up 34 percent,
while exports stood at 252 million US dollars, a growth of 24
percent, according to the regional Department of Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Foreign trade enterprises provided exports worth 147 million US
dollars, or 60 percent of the region's total, to become a major
supplier, while joint ventures contributed 34 million US dollars,
66 percent more than in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Take St. Edenwerss International Enterprises Group Co., Ltd. It
exported over 38 million US dollars worth of cashmere products,
ranking first in China.
</P>
<P>
The autonomous region has also increased efforts to build
export products bases. And as a result, export varieties have been
expanded to 350, 13 of which each collected more than five million
US dollars in exports.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia established foreign trade contacts with Hong Kong,
Macao and Taiwan, Southeast Asia nations and Japan. But now it has
also turned to markets in Europe, North America, Middle East,
Australia, and Africa.  
</P>
</TEXT>
