<HEADLINE> SPAC Urges Pharmaceutical Sector to Develop New Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 16 (Xinhua) -- The State Pharmaceutical
Administration of China (SPAC) has urged Chinese pharmaceutical
companies to attach great importance to developing new drugs to
increase market shares both at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
The administration has called on the sector to inject increased
capital into hi-tech projects and the development of new drugs
during 1998. SPAC sources say the government will provide
additional funding for related efforts.
</P>
<P>
Fifty of the nation's most competent drug manufacturers will be
selected to lead the giant industry which has long been dominated
by the production of medicinal raw materials and imitations of
foreign products.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises will be expected to contribute more than 60
percent of the industry's annual sales volume, and allocate from
3-5 percent of annual sales to developing new products.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investors will be encouraged to invest in hi-tech drug
manufacturing.
</P>
<P>
Some 3,500 Chinese pharmaceutical enterprises currently produce
1,350 types of medicinal raw materials annually, with China
ranking second in the world in terms of both the production and
exports of pharmaceutical materials.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the ongoing national project centers on developing
10 types of new drugs and establishing a network of research
centers to select new drugs, assess safety and conduct clinical
research. 
</P>
</TEXT>
