<HEADLINE> S. Africa Condemns Israeli Decision on West Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 16 (Xinhua) -- South Africa today
condemned a decision of the Israeli cabinet to retain large parts
of the West Bank in any final settlement with the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
"This step by the Israeli cabinet is yet another preemptive
attempt to create facts on the ground, which make a mockery of
the Oslo Accords and sincere efforts to reach negotiated
solutions for a durable peace in the Middle East," South African
Foreign Ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
"The government of Israel must accept that this type of action
can only compound an increasing lack of understanding among the
international community for Israel's cause, ultimately leading to
a further hardening of attitudes and undermining of the very
goals the Netanyahu government states it wishes to achieve."
</P>
<P>
The Israeli cabinet announced Wednesday that certain strategic
positions in West Bank are vital to Israel's national security
and interests and that those positions will never be given up in
negotiations with the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
"The Department (of Foreign Affairs of South Africa) reaffirms
that Israel's occupation and settlement of the West Bank is
illegal in terms of international law and contrary to various
United Nations Security Council resolutions."
</P>
<P>
"Israel therefore has no legitimate pre-existing claim to any
territory, road or water resource in the West Bank," the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
South Africa urged Israel to negotiate with the Palestinians
on this issue.
</P>
<P>
"These issues fall within the parameters of "final status
issues" as defined by the Oslo Accords and must still be
negotiated with the Palestinians." 
</P>
</TEXT>
