<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Shares Surge 3.74 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong share prices surged
3.74 percent on Friday, in a technical rebound after a 7.01
percent slump the previous day on rumors of corporate defaults.
</P>
<P>
The investors had realized they had oversold, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng index rose 321.06 points to close at 8,900.04
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The value of the day's turnover registered at 8,538 million HK
dollars (1,094 million US dollars), down from the 9,181 million HK
dollars (1,177 million US dollars) at the previous day's trading.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index rebounded to 8,726.97 points in early
Friday's trading, gaining 147.99 points, or 1.72 percent, minutes
after the opening bell and it rose 261.04 points, or 3.04 percent,
to close at 8,840.02 at midday.
</P>
<P>
The index had declined 647.57 points to close at 8,578.98 on
Thursday, on rumors that local property developers were defaulting
on loan repayments.
</P>
<P>
But some experts still thought that the market, in spite of the
recent recovery, still lacked a direction amid investors' worries
on higher interest rates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
