<HEADLINE> Double-deck Trains to operate Between Hong Kong, Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Kowloon-Canton
Railway Corporation (KCRC) announced Friday that it will launch a
non-stop daily service between Hong Kong's Hung Hom to the check
point of Lo Wu bordering Hong Kong and Shenzhen starting January
24.
</P>
<P>
Passengers by this new double-deck train, offering a total of
550 seats, will have the immigration formalities processed at Hung
Hom before boarding and then go straight to the Shenzhen border.
</P>
<P>
"The new service offers cross-boundary passengers another
choice and will help relieve the pressure at Lo Wu," said Li Yun
Tai, general manager of the East Rail Operations of the KCRC.
</P>
<P>
KCRC currently operates various through train services between
Hong Kong and cities in China's inland and there are more than 300
trains to and from Lo Wu every day.
</P>
<P>
Fitted with luxurious and state-of-the-art facilities, the
double-deck coaches were manufactured in Japan while the
locomotives were built in Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
This service will be extended to Guangzhou as soon as the
railway between Shenzhen and Guangzhou has been fully electrified,
Li said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
