<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Type of Public Bus Put in Use in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 16 (Xinhua) -- A new type of 20-seat bus that
are most suitable to Macao's narrow roads was put into use here on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
With a capacity of accommodating 49 passengers at the peak
period, the new bus is one meter longer, 0.30 meter wider and
0.135 meter higher than the 20-seat bus currently in use in
Macao. It is said to be the first of its kind in Macao, Hong Kong
and China's inland.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the new bus can best cope with Macao's roads,
which are characterized by its narrowness, sharp turns and
countless oneways. The densely-populated peninsula have some roads
which, when a bus moves ahead, no one can go by the bus.
</P>
<P>
Liu Hei Wan, managing director of the Transmac Public Bus
Company, said it is worthwhile although the new "Benz" brand bus
costs two to three times as much the old 20-seat bus bought from
Japan.
</P>
<P>
"The new bus can carry more people at the peak time and
passengers are more comfortable on it," he told reporters at a
ceremony on Friday. "Passengers will also have more convenience in
getting on and off the bus."
</P>
<P>
Transmac and the Macao Public Bus Company are the two public
bus companies in Macao. Together they run more than 30 lines in
Macao Peninsula and its two islands. Public bus is the most
favored form of public transportation in Macao as it is
comfortable, convenient, and cheap. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
