<HEADLINE> More Victims Added to Pastor Murder List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 16 (Xinhua) -- At least seven more victims
have been added to the suspected murder list of Hungary-born
pastor Andras Pandy, increasing the total to 13 now.
</P>
<P>
The addition came out as a result of initial laboratory
analysis of the human remains exhumed from within the houses of
the pastor last September in the Belgian capital city, according
to local television RTBF reports today.
</P>
<P>
Analysis, carried out at the KUL Human Heredity Research
Center, showed that the remains belonged to none of the six
reported missing members of the Pandy family.
</P>
<P>
The two ex-wives and four of the pastor's eight children were
feared killed by the pastor though Pandy claimed that they had
returned to Hungary where local police has been tracing their
whereabouts.
</P>
<P>
The six Pandy family members were reported missing between 1986
and 1989.
</P>
<P>
Agnes Pandy, the eldest daughter of the pastor also detained by
the Belgian police on charges of assistance in the murder case,
told the police that the bodies of the six family members had been
dissolved in acid.
</P>
<P>
The new murder victims found in Pandy's houses were feared to
have come from Hungary.
</P>
<P>
Investigators have been trying to identify the victims but the
task proved to be difficult in that starting from 1980 more than
1,000 people had been reported missing in this country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
