<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Comes First in Women's 4x100m Medley Relay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 16 (Xinhua) -- The United States splashed home
first at the women's 4x100m medley relay at the world swimming
championships here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The American foursome, anchored by Olympic champion Amy van
Dyken, clocked 4:01.93, beating Australia into second place.
</P>
<P>
The Australians, anchored by Susie O'Neil, timed 4:05.12.
</P>
<P>
Japan finished third in 4:06.27.
</P>
<P>
Germany, Hungary, the Netherlands and Britain placed fourth to
seventh. Belgium was disqualified. 
</P>
