<HEADLINE> Urban Construction Archives Develop Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 16 (Xinhua) -- China's urban construction
archives have developed rapidly and have effectively promoted the
sound development of urban construction in line with rapid
urbanization.
</P>
<P>
The 1,500 construction archives nationwide have played an
indispensable role in strengthening urban design, planning,
mapping, prospecting and land management, in addition to helping
settle disputes regarding the ownership of real estate, according
to a senior official with the Ministry of Construction.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics indicate that the country's construction
archives bureau yielded economic benefits totalling some 1.5
billion yuan between 1993 and 1996. Some 730,000 people reviewed
well over 1.65 million archival documents during the four year
period. 
</P>
