<HEADLINE> China Has Its Own National Geographical Magazine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 16 (Xinhua) -- China has its own national
geographical magazine beginning this year, with a major revision
of the periodical "Geographical Knowledge," which is a favorite of
many Chinese youngsters.
</P>
<P>
The periodical, following the example of the popular American
magazine, "National Geographic," has expanded its pages to 84,
which are filled with colorful pictures.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that "Geographical Knowledge" is a "real national
geographical magazine of China" after reading the first issue of
this year.
</P>
<P>
The magazine's coverage has expanded to natural, economic and
human geography, which includes the evolution of the universe, the
formation of landforms and the discovery of scientific
investigation and research.
</P>
<P>
The magazine's first issue of this year has carried interesting
stories such as "Society of the Giant Panda" and "To See the
Sorcerer's Dance In Tibet."
</P>
<P>
Li Shuanke, director of the magazine, said that China has the
largest number of scientists and educators, and thus has the
capacity to produce a national geographical magazine.
</P>
<P>
The magazine, sponsored by the Chinese Geographic Society and
the Geographic Institute of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, is
one of the most influential popular science periodicals in the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
