<HEADLINE> Klim Wins Men's 100m Butterfly Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Australia's world record holder
Michael Klim won his fifth medal at the world swimming
championships as he triumphed in the men's 100m butterfly final
here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Klim, who had won the 200m freestyle and 4x200 freestyle relay
gold medals and as many silver going into this race, timed 52.25
seconds to touch home first, just 0.1 second outside of his world
mark set in last year's Australian trials for the world
championships.
</P>
<P>
Sweden's Lars Frolander clocked 52.79 for the silver medal
while Australian Geoff Huegill got the bronze in 52.90. 
