<HEADLINE> EU to Aid Cambodian Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, January 16 (Xinhua) -- The European Union will
provide 9.5 million European Currency Units (ECU) (about 10.5
million U.S. dollars) in aid for Cambodia's July elections, said
an EU official for East Asia affairs.
</P>
<P>
Under an accord that needs a last signature from Cambodia's
Co-Minister of Interior Sar Kheng on Friday, the EU will
contribute 8.3 million ECU to Cambodia's electoral process, 0.1
million ECU to the training of local media and 1.1 million ECU to
the provision of an independent European Observation Unit
throughout the elections.
</P>
<P>
The EU's director for East Asia Gwyn Morgan and Cambodia's
Co-Minister of Interior You Hockry already signed the agreement
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"The EU reserves the right to suspend its activities on the
electoral register if the other key factors which would permit the
holding of free and fair elections were not also put into place,"
the EU said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia needs 21 million U.S. dollars for its forthcoming
July 26 elections, the first since the U.N.-sponsored national
elections in 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
