<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India to Introduce Eurotrain Explorer Pass Scheme </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 16 (Xinhua)-- India is to introduce a
Eurotrain Explorer Pass Scheme (EEPS) for foreign National and
non-resident Indians, similar to Indrail Pass, against payment in
foreign exchange to attract more foreign tourists, the Railway
Ministry announced here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The scheme was formulated following a proposal from
Denmark-based M/S Eurotrain International for introduction of
explorer pass on Indian railways. Under the scheme, an explorer
pass holder will get the pass exchanged at pre-determined
locations in India with Indrail pass before traveling on Indian
railways.
</P>
<P>
Simultaneously, railways have decided to expand the network for
sale of Indrail pass in collaboration with Air India and Indian
Airlines. This strategic alliance with two national air carriers
will go a long way to offer an air-cum-rail ticket to travelers
residing abroad, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Indrail pass scheme has been introduced to facilitate foreign
tourists to travel on Indian railways without any restriction of
mileage or number of trips during the validity of the pass. At
present, Indrail passes are sold at important stations in India
and in 13 foreign countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
