<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Allow Citizens to Have Dual Nationality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 16 (Xinhua)-- Vietnamese citizens are entitled
to relinquish their Vietnamese nationality when they are also of
another nationality or they can have dual nationality, it was
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
This was announced in a government decree issued Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The amendments will replace relevant provisions of Vietnam's
nationality decree issued on February 5, 1990.
</P>
<P>
Under the new decree, those who want to gain, relinquish, or to
restore Vietnamese nationality must apply to the people's
committees of the provinces or cities where they are living, or to
the Vietnamese diplomatic or consular representations in the
countries of their residence, or directly to the Vietnamese
Ministry of Justice. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
