<HEADLINE> American Grote Wins Men's 200 Breaststroke Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 16 (Xinhua) -- World top-ranked Kurt Grote of
the United States beat Frenchman Jean-Christophe Sarnin at the pad
to win the men's 200m breaststroke final at the world swimming
championships here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Grote, who got the lead at 100m and conceded it to the
Frenchman at 150m, surged ahead in the final meters to clock a
winning time of two minutes and 13.40 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Sarnin, just 0.02 seconds away from the American, got the
silver medal.
</P>
<P>
Hungarian Norbert Rozsa finished third in 2:13.59.
</P>
<P>
Grote, 24, was the triple gold medalist at last year's Pan
Pacific championships, the most important event of 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
