<HEADLINE> Wu Yanyan Wins Women's 200 Individual Medley </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 16 (Xinhua) -- World record holder Wu Yanyan of
China led all the way to snatch the women's 200m individual medley
title at the world swimming championships here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old Chinese clocked two minutes and 10.88 seconds,
1.16 seconds outside her world mark of 2:09.72 set in the Chinese
National Games last year.
</P>
<P>
Her winning time is 0.90 better than the 16-year-old world
championship record.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Chen Yan, new world champion in both the 400m freestyle
and 400m individual medley, picked up the silver medal in 2:13.66.
</P>
<P>
Martina Moravcova of the Czech Republic, winner of this
morning's heats, got the bronze in 2:14.26. 
