<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-16 09:47 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 44.55 Kilograms of Heroin Seized in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 16 (Xinhua) -- A total of 44.55 kilograms of
pure heroin have been seized in an anti-drug operation in Turkish
eastern province of Van, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
It said that acting on a tip-off, the Turkish police followed
a passenger bus from Van province linking Iran to Turkey's
largest city of Istanbul and found the heroin in 45 parcels
hidden in the vehicle. However, it did not say when the heroin
was confiscated.
</P>
<P>
The police detained the driver of the bus and two other
suspects and have staged operations in pursuit of six other
people in connection with the drug smuggling, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is a key transit route of drugs to Europe from the area
bordering Afghanistan and Pakistan. In 1996, Turkish police
seized 4.4 tonnes of heroin, or 40 percent of the world's total
haul. 
</P>
</TEXT>
