<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 16 (Xinhua) -- One Turk was killed and
two others injured Friday when an avalanche happened in
northeastern Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the three people were hunting wild pigs
at Efeler village in Borcka town of Artvin province bordering
Georgia when the avalanche occurred.
</P>
<P>
One of them died and the other two who were slightly injured
were rescued from the avalanche, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
It added that the injured had been hospitalized and in
good conditions. 
