<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Financially-Troubled Enterprises in Tianjin Raising Efficiency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 16 (Xinhua) -- The economic performance of 177
financially-troubled industrial firms in Tianjin, or more than
half of the city's money-losing enterprises, took a favorable turn
in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Sixty-five of them have eliminated deficits, said an
official of the Tianjin Municipal Economic Commission.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin, an old industrial center, has 323 money-losing
enterprises which turn out less competitive products as a result of
obsolete equipment and poor management.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government take 20 measures last year to assist
those enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 22 such firms received 17 million yuan in loans for
use as operating capital. Consequently, their output value
increased by 18 percent and sales by 16 percent last year. Three
enterprises formerly in the red are now reporting profits.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 1,200 redundant workers have either been urged to
retire or channeled into the service trade sector to
alleviate the burden of those enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
