<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-British Joint-Venture Glass Company Profitable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 16 (Xinhua) -- China's first large building
materials joint venture, the Shanghai Yaohua-Pilkington Glass Co Ltd,
has been profitable over the past 10 years, with its total assets
now 4.4 times that 10 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-British joint venture built its first floating glass
production line with an annual capacity of 700 tons in December
1987, the largest of its kind in China. It added another
production line in 1993 with an investment of 700 million yuan
(85.4 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The company has just completed the expansion of its workshop
area which covers 54,000 square meters. With nine production
lines, it has now built an annual capacity of 280,000 tons of
floating glass and six million square meters of ordinary glass.
</P>
<P>
Its products are well sold in the domestic market and exported to
more than 30 countries and regions, with an average export ratio of
43 percent.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 10 years, the company has had accumulated sales
income of 4.26 billion yuan (519 million US dollars) with a total
profit of 1.51 billion yuan (184 million US dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
