<HEADLINE> Wells Remain Free of Contamination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 16 (Xinhua) -- The Zhangjiakou
Environmental Protection Bureau has guaranteed potable well water
for homeless people and relief workers in the earthquake-stricken
areas.
</P>
<P>
The bureau has closely monitored wells since the devastating
January 10 earthquake which measured 6.2 on the Richter Scale,
with bureau officials reporting that wells remain free of
contamination.
</P>
<P>
Water samples from three sites in Zhangbei County, the most
seriously damaged area in the epic center, and technological
analyses prove the continuing potability of well water, according
to officials.
</P>
<P>
Seismologists noted that earthquakes often create negative
changes of both chemical elements and the hardness of water.
</P>
</TEXT>
