<HEADLINE> Farmers in Ethnic Area Active in Learning Skills </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, January 16 (Xinhua) -- More than 10,000 farmers in an
area of southwest China's Guizhou Province, where the ethnic
groups of Buyi and Miao are mainly distributed, have received
"green certificates" since 1994.
</P>
<P>
The certificates, given by the government of Qiannan Buyi and
Miao Autonomous Prefecture in the southern part of Guizhou, show
the farmers have mastered certain farming techniques after
training.
</P>
<P>
Despite the relatively poor economy compared with east coastal
areas, local government encourages their farmers to learn
scientific agricultural knowledge and apply it.
</P>
<P>
The province launched a "green certificates project" in 1994 to
train local farmers in agricultural skills.
</P>
<P>
Some 11,116 farmers took part in the training through 1997,
most of whom passed the examinations for their "green
certificates." 
</P>
</TEXT>
