<HEADLINE> Zhupyna Lifts Second Gold in Diving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine's Olena Zhupyna snatched
her second gold medal from the current World Swimming
Championships as she combined with Svitlana Serbina to win the
women's synchronized diving event on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Zhupyna, the new 3m springboard world champion, and her
17-year-old partner, posted 278.28 points from the five-dive
final, beating the Chinese duo of Chen Li and Cai Yuyan by less
than two points.
</P>
<P>
Cai and Chen, who finished behind the 24-year-old Zhupyna in
Monday's 3m springboard final, registered 276.54 points and got
the silver medal.
</P>
<P>
The American pair of Kristin Link and Linday Long grabbed the
bronze with a collection of 265.47 points.
</P>
<P>
The Ukrainian combination nailed their position after the third
dive which won 68.88 points. The Chinese duo scored better than
the Ukrainians in the last two dives but they were not good enough
to overtake the leaders.
</P>
<P>
The French team of Julie Danaux and Odile Arboles finished
fourth in 263.67 points, just 2.02 over Germany's Ute Wetzig and
Anke Piper who came fifth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
