<HEADLINE> East China Province Speeding Up Urban Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, January 16 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province
maintained its momentum in urban construction last year, with an
investment of 3.3 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
As a result, 28 percent of local people have now lived in
cities and towns; 95 percent of urban residents have access to tap
water and 60 percent to natural gas; and 29 percent of urban areas
in the province is covered with trees or grass.
</P>
<P>
Of the province's 22 cities, 21 have finished work on general
urban planning. A number of key infrastructure construction
projects were completed last year. Among them were two
refuse-incinerated furnaces with a handling capacity of 50 tons
each.
</P>
<P>
The province raised money for urban construction from different
channels such as using overseas investment, issuing bonds and
levying vehicle administration fees.
</P>
<P>
The province set a record by introducing 80 million
U.S. dollars of overseas investment into the sector in 1997.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
