<HEADLINE> Township Enterprises in Tibet Filled with New Lease of Life </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Township enterprises in the Tibet
Autonomous Region are striving to increase cooperation and
exchanges with their counterparts in the inland areas through
various forms in an effort to boost economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics said that the autonomous region introduced a
total of 76.5 million yuan (9.21 million US dollars) and 42
projects last year, and basically formed a range of industries
involving farming and animal husbandry products processing,
mining, building material, transportation and the catering trade.
</P>
<P>
Since the central government held the third conference on the
work of Tibet in 1994, a boom of helping Tibet has surged across
the country.
</P>
<P>
Under the principles of mutual benefit and common development,
and cooperations in providing funds, technology, talents and
information between Tibet and China's inland areas are carried out
on a broad scale.
</P>
<P>
The Lhasa city government organized many township entrepreneurs
on a tour of inland areas last year and signed contracts worth 200
million yuan (24.1 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the region sent more than 100 prefectural, county
and township officials to Beijing municipality, and Guangdong and
Shandong provinces on an investigative tour, and some 1,000 people
from Tibet received training on business administration in inland
areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
