<HEADLINE> North China Province to Promote Service Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 16 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei
Province plans to promote its service trade sector over the next
three years.
</P>
<P>
Plans call for the service trade to account for some 34 percent
of the province's GDP by the year 2000, with more than 28 percent
of local laborers working in the sector.
</P>
<P>
The province will not only continue to improve its commodity
circulation, transportation, telecommunications and financial
sectors, but also place increased emphasis on developing
local tourism.
</P>
<P>
Efforts will also focus on the development of the local
information industry, with main efforts centered on
telecommunications networks and information equipment
manufacturing.
</P>
<P>
The province will standardize local real estate development,
accelerate the renovation of old houses and the construction of
new urban areas. Hebei will also introduce the accumulated funds
system for housing to a large number of enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
