<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Set up National Education Council </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam decided Thursday to set
up a national education council to help the prime minister guide
the implementation of the strategy on education and training in
the nation's industrialization process.
</P>
<P>
According to a decision signed by Vietnam's prime minister, the
council will be responsible for leading the review of education
reform.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Phan Van Khai will head the council, while the
minister of education and training will serve as permanent vice
chairman, and the director of the ruling party's central
committee's commission for science and education, vice chairman.
</P>
<P>
Members of the council include the chairman of the national
assembly's committee for culture, education, youth and children as
well as four leading ministers of the government.
</P>
<P>
The council is to evaluate major policies on education and
training and authorizes matters within the power of the prime
minister.
</P>
<P>
The decision will take effect at the beginning of the next
month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
