Sixth-ranked Chinese Dai Yun shocked European champion Carmilla
Martin of Denmark to set up an all-Chinese semi-final against
world champion Ye Zhaoying at the Japan Open badminton tournament.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old Chinese took the advantage when fourth-ranked
Martin temporarily lost her concentration at 5-4 in a close
beginning, and raced to an 11-6, 11-1 victory in 22 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Ye comfortably beat Kim Ji-Hyun of South Korea 11-4,
11-3.
</P>
<P>
China took another semi-final berth when second seeded Gong
Zhichao fought off Lee Joo-Hyun of South Korea for a 7-11, 11-3,
11-6 win. 
