<DOCNO> XIE19980116.0244 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Reports Good Foreign Trade Results for 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, January 16 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang
Province, which is widely known as the home of Chinese silk and
satin, recorded a foreign trade volume of 15.2 billion
U.S. dollars in 1997, up 13 percent on the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang's 1997 export value climbed 18.6 percent to 11 billion
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang, one of China's most important foreign trade
powerhouses, offers numerous advantages in terms of manufacturing
and processing, according to an official from the Provincial
Commission of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Products manufactured in the province have entered the
international market, with some 20 percent of Zhejiang's total
output sold overseas. The province has established trade ties with
more than 180 countries and regions, according to Yang Zucheng,
director of the commission.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that foreign trade accounts for 27.5
percent of Zhejiang's gross domestic product (GDP). Exports
accounted for 20 percent of the province's 1997 GDP.  
</P>
</TEXT>
