<HEADLINE> China Eastern Airlines to Resume Flight to Nagoya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 16 (Xinhua) -- With the approval of the Civil
Aviation Administration of China, Shanghai-based China Eastern
Airlines will resume its flights to Nagoya, Japan, on Feb. 7.
</P>
<P>
The company will operate one flight every Wednesday and
Friday. Planes will depart Shanghai in the morning and return in
the afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The company is the second in China to operate on the
Shanghai-Nagoya air route. The other is China Northwestern
Airlines based in Xi'an, capital of Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
China Eastern Airlines already has flights linking Shanghai
with the Japanese cities of Tokyo, Osaka, Fukuoka, and
Nagasaki. 
