<HEADLINE> More Foreign Funds Invested in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Beijing has reported remarkable
progress in introducing foreign funds, according to a local
official in charge of international trade and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The official said that in 1997 Beijing approved 790
foreign-funded enterprises involving 2.52 billion U.S. dollars of
contracted foreign investment, or an increase of 12.7 percent over
1996.
</P>
<P>
The official disclosed that 61.9 percent of the involved
foreign funds went into electronic telecommunications, computer
automation, biological engineering and laser instruments.
</P>
<P>
The number of projects funded by 146 international companies
has reached 404. Those projects involve a combined foreign
investment of 3.38 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The total amount of foreign investment for 1997 hit a record
2.59 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The official attributed the increase in foreign investment to
the improvement of local financial environment and the passing of
a series of preferential policies on introducing foreign funds.
</P>
</TEXT>
