<HEADLINE> Beijing to Set Up Software Garden </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Beijing has planned to
establish a software garden in suburban Daxing County, in a bid to
promote the development of the local software industry.
</P>
<P>
The scheduled space of the garden will be 1,000 mu (66.66
hectares). The first phase project will occupy 50 mu (3.33
hectares) and is expected to be completed within two years and a
half.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that the first phase project can provide posts
for 20,000 software engineers, and can produce an annual output
value of 6.6 billion yuan (795 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Beijing is China's largest software development base, with the
over 10,000 specialists trained in this regard and some 100
computer and information centers.
</P>
<P>
The city's combined transaction volume of computer software and
hardware accounts for 70 percent of the country's total. 
</P>
</TEXT>
