<HEADLINE> US Ambassador Presents Earthquake Relief Supplies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Ambassador of the United States
to China James R. Sasser presented 40 tons of earthquake relief
supplies and 25,000 US dollars of funds to China here today.
</P>
<P>
These relief supplies for the Hebei Provincial department of
Civil Affairs, which were drawn from the US military stocks valued
at about half a million US dollars, include blankets, medical
supplies, warm clothing, sleeping bags, shoes, parkas, and
humanitarian rations.
</P>
<P>
The funds will be disbursed through the Chinese Ministry of
Civil Affairs and the United Nations Development Program, which
are coordinating international donations.
</P>
<P>
At a ceremony held here at noon, Sasser, on behalf of US
President Clinton and the American people, expressed his country's
sympathy for the victims of the earthquake in Hebei and the
terrible losses they have suffered.
</P>
<P>
He said that "Americans admire the courage and indomitable
spirit of the people of Hebei in facing this tragedy", and "I hope
that our contributions will help them rebuild their homes and
their lives".  
