and many other buildings, was badly damaged when a truck-bomb
exploded in the hotel's car park. The bombing attack, carried out
by a group of Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam rebels, killed at
least 18 people and injured more than 100 others on October 15,
1997.
</P>
