<HEADLINE> Poland Inflation Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, January 15 (Xinhua) -- Poland's inflation rate was 13.2
percent in 1997, a 5.3 percent decline from 1996, the national
statistics bureau said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The inflation rate in December, 1997 went down 13.2 percent
from the same period in 1996, 0.2 percent more than expected.
</P>
<P>
Commodity prices and charges for consumer services in 1997
increased 14.9 percent over 1996, 0.1 percent lower than expected.
</P>
<P>
Food prices rose 10.2 percent last December, compared with 19
percent in the last month of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Prices rose 12 percent for non-food commodities in 1997, while
in 1996 they rose 17.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Poland has enjoyed a decline in inflation rate for seven
successive years since 1991. 
</P>
