<DOCNO> XIE19980116.0295 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Introduce New Loan Classification System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 16 (Xinhua) -- China is to apply a new loan
classification system from the end of this year in line with
international practice, according to China's leading banking
official.
</P>
<P>
Dai Xianglong, governor of the People's Bank of China, made the
remarks in a press conference this morning.
</P>
<P>
Dai told the press that the new system will classify loans into
five categories, including "standard, special mention, substandard,
doubtful and loss."
</P>
<P>
The introduction of the new system is aimed at tackling the
existing problems in China's financial sector, such as high
proportion of problem loans of the state commercial banks,
remaining problems of non-bank financial institutions, illegal
establishment of financial institutions by some localities and
departments, and unlicensed financial business activities. "These
deep-rooted problems reflect the unrevolved structural imbalances
in the economy," Dai noted.
</P>
<P>
China has already launched an overall investigation on the
risks of financial institutions. On-going monitoring was imposed
on financial institutions with high risks. "Financial risks that
had already cropped up were timely dealt with and mitigated," Dai
pointed out.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that another two years of efforts will bring
loan management of the Chinese commercial banks to a "relatively
high standard," Dai said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
