<HEADLINE> MPs to Oversee Transport Services in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan Transport and
Highways Minister A. H. M. Fowzie has asked 93 MPs to supervise
the country's transport services in a bid to eliminate corruption
and malpractice in the transport sector.
</P>
<P>
Officials in the Transport and Highways Ministry said Friday
that letters of appointment have already been sent to the MPs,
granting them the necessary authority.
</P>
<P>
The MPs are required to visit the bus depots in their
constituencies regularly and make reports on their own
observations to officials in charge of the country's transport
affairs.
</P>
<P>
The move is aimed at strengthening supervision over the sector
to deter increasing corruption and malpractice in the transport
services, which have aroused widespread dissatisfaction among the
people, the officials added.  
