<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, January 15 (Xinhua) -- Brazil has issued 100
million U.S. dollars worth of bonds on the Portuguese market, the
Brazilian Bank of Discount has announced.
</P>
<P>
The bonds, issued on Wednesday, are redeemable in three years
and have an annual interest of 8.08 percent, the Folha de Sao
Paulo newspaper said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
