<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Strengthen Role of Financial Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 16 (Xinhua) -- China is to give more financial
supports to agriculture, state-enterprise reform and housing this
year, said China's leading banking official in a press conference
held this morning.
</P>
<P>
Dai Xianglong, governor of the People's Bank of China, told the
press that no less than 10 percent of the credit growth of
the state banks will be ear-marked for agricultural
development. Loans granted by the rural credit cooperatives for
the sector should also be gradually increased in the years ahead.
</P>
<P>
Also, priority will continue to be given to the large and
medium-sized state enterprises. Meanwhile, the state banks are
expected to support small enterprises in their restructuring as
well as the development of non-state sector, said Dai.
</P>
<P>
Dai noted that a residential housing financial service system
will be developed to foster a housing market. "Mortgage business
will be expanded to cater to the needs of more customers and
credit ceilings imposed on 'basic housing projects' will be
removed," he said.
</P>
<P>
Dai pointed out that efforts will also be made to restrict bank
loans to luxury real estate projects so as to prevent bubble
elements in the economy.
</P>
<P>
Domestic foreign exchange loan facilities will be developed to
expand domestic and international markets, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
