<HEADLINE> Yeltsin's Spokesman Criticizes Duma's Delay on START-2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 15 (Xinhua) -- Russian President's Press
Secretary Sergi Yastrzhembsky Thursday criticized the delayed
ratification of the second Strategic Arms Reduction Treaty
(START-2) by the State Duma, the lower house of parliament.
</P>
<P>
He told a press conference here that the delay does not conform
to the on-going Russian military reform and will have a negative
impact on the Russian-United States relations.
</P>
<P>
He said the postponement of ratifying the START-2 will also
affect the further progress of the strategic arms reduction
treaty, which is in the interests of Russia.
</P>
<P>
The START-2 was signed by Russia and the U.S. in early
1993. The U.S. Senate ratified the treaty in 1996, but the Russian
State Duma has failed to endorse it so far.
</P>
<P>
United States President Bill Clinton has said that he refused
to visit Russia before its ratification of the treaty. 
</P>
