<HEADLINE> Shopping in Guangzhou Becomes More Convenient </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, a leading shopping
center in south China, is believed to have the largest number of
shops and department stores per capita in the country.
</P>
<P>
Latest figures show the capital of Guangdong Province has
260,000 retail outlets, or one for every 25 people.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports indicated that Shanghai, China's largest
commercial city, has 160,000 retail outlets, averaging one for
every 80 people.
</P>
<P>
During the last three years, Guangzhou has built more than 660
chain stores and more than 60 indoor vegetable and meat markets,
in addition to a large number of shopping malls, convenience
stores and boutiques. Warehouse stores are springing up not only
along major streets but also in newly built residential areas.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the city's retail sales exceeded 80 billion yuan
(9.638 billion U.S. dollars), up 10 percent over 1996 to rank
third in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
