<HEADLINE> CPPCC Fujian Committee Handles More Proposals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, January 16 (Xinhua) -- The Fujian Provincial Committee
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC)
has handled an escalating number of proposals with its members'
increasing enthusiasm in participating in political and government
affairs.
</P>
<P>
At the first session of the Eighth CPPCC Fujian Provincial
Committee that just closed, 663 proposals had been received,
including 513 from its 435 CPPCC members.
</P>
<P>
The proposals concern focused work as well as hot issues and
difficulties, such as the reform of state-owned enterprises, the
status of agriculture as a fundamental industry, anti-corruption
and cooperation among Fujian, Taiwan and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
After careful examination by related departments, 621 proposals
-- 93.6 percent of the total -- have been put on file for further
investigation and solution, and 30 cases have been listed as key
bills. 
</P>
