<HEADLINE> Beijing Destroys Pirated CDs, VCDs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 16 (Xinhua) -- More than 230,000 pornographic
or pirated compact discs (CDs), video CDs and CD-ROMs were crushed
by a steam roller yesterday in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Some 45,000 banned or pirated publications were turned into
pulp simultaneously. The operation was jointly organized by the
Beijing Municipal Radio and Television Bureau, Press and
Publication Bureau and Public Security Bureau, according to
today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has stepped up efforts last year to strengthen
supervision over the book, audiovisual and electronic publication
market. The law enforcement department has confiscated over
300,000 illegal audiovisual and electronic products, and 650,000
illegal publications in the capital.
</P>
<P>
A new round of campaign against illegal publications has been
launched in Beijing and other parts of the country at the
beginning of the new year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
