<HEADLINE> Russia to Boost Inter-Governmental Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 15 (Xinhua) -- The Russian government decided
Thursday to strengthen inter-governmental trade and economic
cooperation with other countries, ITAA-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Russia could better protect its foreign trade companies through
bilateral cooperation with its partners in inter-governmental
trade and economic cooperation committees, said Mikhail Fradkov,
the minister of foreign economic relations and trade.
</P>
<P>
Russia should attract more foreign investment and technologies,
as well as protect its domestic market, Fradkov said.
</P>
<P>
Interfax quoted Fradkov as saying that Russia would take
important measures to protect its domestic market in the near
future.
</P>
<P>
He hoped inter-governmental trade and economic cooperation
committees would contribute to avoiding trade conflicts between
Russia and its trade partners.
</P>
<P>
Russia has set up inter-governmental trade and economic
cooperation committees with about 70 countries outside the former
Soviet Union countries up to now. 
</P>
