<HEADLINE> China's Banking Sector Sees Smooth Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 16 (Xinhua) -- China's banking sector has
witnessed a smooth development in 1997 in spite of the financial
crisis in Asian emerging industrial countries, central bank
governor Dai Xianglong said here today.
</P>
<P>
Total deposits rose by 18.6 percent to reach 8,240 billion
yuan last year while outstanding loans chalked up an increase of
16.7 percent to 7,490 billion yuan, Dai told a press conference.
</P>
<P>
Throughout the year, broad money (M2) grew by 17.3 percent and
notes in circulation (M0) expanded by 15.6 percent, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
