<HEADLINE> Spain to Strengthen Military Ties With NATO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, January 15 (Xinhua) -- Spain wants more of its officers
to be in the headquarters of the North Atlantic Treaty
organization (NATO) and its ties with the Allied Command of
Atlantic to be promoted.
</P>
<P>
This was indicated by Spanish Prime Minister Jose Maria Aznar
during his meeting Thursday with visiting Supreme Allied Commander
Harlod Gehman.
</P>
<P>
Admiral Gehman arrived here Thursday on his first visit to
Spain after he was appointed as the allied commander last
September.
</P>
<P>
Gehman also held talks with Spanish Minister of Defense Eduard
Serra Rexach Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference held after their talks, both Gehman and
Serra stressed that the decision of Spain to fully join in the
military alliance would benefit both sides because of Spain's
strategic location between the Atlantic Ocean and the
Mediterranean Sea.
</P>
<P>
The supreme allied commander is scheduled to visit the capitals
of other allied nations later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
