<HEADLINE> Sanchez Vicario Stops Williams' Winning Run </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Arantxa Sanchez Vicario broke
the hope for the Williams sisters' finals by beating younger
Williams in the semifinal of the Sydney international tennis
tournament on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The 26-year-old Spaniard blew away Serena Williams, 10 years
junior, 6-2, 6-1 within one hour in her warm-up for the coming
Australian Open.
</P>
<P>
The fifth-seeded and ninth-ranked Sanchez Vicario is likely to
face 17-year-old Venus Williams in Saturday's final. Venus was due
to play Japan's Ai Sugiyama in the second semifinal later on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Serena, the more talented of the prodigal sisters, blamed the
defeat on pains in her right knee and leg after playing seven
matches in eight days. 
