<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Tobacco Industry Sets Profit Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 16 (Xinhua) -- China's tobacco industry set an
all time high record in its pre-tax profit, which stood at 90
billion yuan (10.84 billion US dollars), despite the fact that the
production nd sales of cigarettes slumped in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The figure was up 8.4 percent from that in 1996, which saw the
figure hit 83 billion yuan, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The industry turned out 1,683.55 billion cigarettes last year,
down one percent from the previous year. The sales reached 1,694.7
billion cigarettes in 1997, down 0.4 percent from that a year
earlier.
</P>
<P>
"The saturated market, fake products, rampant smuggling plus
people's increasing awareness of health have combined to restrict
the production level of the tobacco industry," the newspaper
quoted Zhou Ruizeng, spokesman for the State Tobacco Monopoly
Administration, as saying.
</P>
<P>
However, improvement in technology and increase in quality
brands have ensured the sector's tax revenues "going up", which
account for one-tenth of the country's total fiscal income, Zhou
said.
</P>
<P>
And the advanced equipment and technical renovation has made
the industry's profits rise up 4.5 percent to 11.78 billion yuan
last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
