<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 16 (Xinhua) -- The following are highlights of
major Beijing-based newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
"People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- President Jiang Zemin attended a forum yesterday discussing
the newly published Military writings of Luo Ronghuan, one of the
founders of the People's Liberation Army who fought to expand the
revolutionary bases and the Communist Party of China's armed
forces before 1949.
</P>
<P>
Jiang asked to learn from the late Marshal Luo's glorious
deeds, revolutionary thinking, and lofty morals, and called him a
faithful fighter, a tested proletarian revolutionary and
strategist, an outstanding Party, state, and army leader.
</P>
<P>
-- Premier Li Peng yesterday said that China's oil industry
should continue its policy of "stablizing production in the east
and developing oil production in the west," speed up oil
exploration, and explore domestic and international markets.
</P>
<P>
Li, meeting with delegates to a China National Petroleum
Corporation conference, thanked the industry's employees for
their enormous contribution to the national economy last year with
their new developments in exploration, production, and research.
</P>
<P>
The utilization of overseas oil resources should become an
important part of future development of the country's oil
industry, Li told delegates to a national conference of China
National Petroleum Corporation.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- President Jiang Zemin told a group of provincial publicity
departments officials yesterday that publicity departments should
do a practical and active job of holding the banner of Deng
Xiaoping Theory high.
</P>
<P>
Building socialism with Chinese characteristics was the theme
of the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) and the Party's work theme.
</P>
<P>
He asked publicity departments to help promote a new upsurge of
studying Deng Xiaoping Theory among the masses, and to sum up the
experience they gained in the efforts to combine the Party Central
Committee's line and policies with local realities, emancipating
their minds, and seeking truth from facts.
</P>
<P>
-- Wei Jianxing, a member of the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China Central
Committee, told a national meeting on cultural and ethical
progress yesterday that there must be continued efforts in
cultural and ethical work.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The Ministry of Labor will carry out occupational training
programs for the estimated 10 million laid-off workers across the
country in three years to help them find new jobs.
</P>
<P>
The strategy is to improve trainees' work skills and enhance
their capacity to find new jobs. One measure is to establish
"re-employment funds" in various places. Displaced workers from
the sectors of textile, military projects, machine-building
and coal mining will have priority to take part in the training
program.
</P>
<P>
-- China appealed yesterday for holding a dialogue to settle
differences regarding the United Nations' weapons inspections in
Iraq, said Foreign Ministry spokesman Shen Guofang yesterday.
</P>
</TEXT>
