<HEADLINE> Frenchman Saby Wins 14th Stage in Paris-Dakar Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 15 (Xinhua) -- Frenchman Bruno Saby continued
his dominance in the Paris-Dakar rally by winning the 14th stage
in the Mauritanian desert on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Saby, of Mitsubishi, was two minutes ahead of reigning champion
Kenjiro Shinozuka of Japan in the 358-km leg from Tidjikja to Atar
across the Chinguetti dunes.
</P>
<P>
Jean-Pierre Fontenay who finished runner-up to Shinozuka last
year, was third with three minutes 40 seconds behind Saby.
</P>
<P>
However, Fontenay retained the lead of more than 40 minutes he
gained in Wednesday's marathon stage.
</P>
<P>
In the motorcycle class, Dutchman Gerard Jimmick won a new
stage victory, with nearly six minutes faster than Italian
Fabrizio Meoni.
</P>
<P>
Meoni was a minute faster than Frenchman Stephane Peterhansel,
who was fourth behind South African Alfie Cox.
</P>
<P>
But the Frenchman remained more than half an hour ahead of his
closest rival Meoni in the overall standings.
</P>
<P>
Compatriot Richard Sainct, second overall two days ago, dropped
out of the race more than halfway through the stage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
