<HEADLINE> Russia, Norway win World Cup Biathlon Races </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 15 (Xinhua) -- Olga Romasko of Russia and Halvard
Hanevold of Norway clinched their first wins of the season, taking
the World Cup biathlon races in Anterselva, Italy on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Veteran Romasko, winner of last season's World Cup title in the
7.5km distance, missed two targets to complete the 15km race in 45
minutes 52.3 seconds, enjoying a lead of more than one minute
against runner-up Liv Grete Skjelbreid of Norway.
</P>
<P>
Magdalena Forsberg of Sweden finished third to pull ahead in
the World Cup standings wherein she had 228 points compared to 181
for Galina Koukleva of Russia.
</P>
<P>
Ricco Gross of Germany, overall leader in the men's World Cup
standing, finished second in the 20km distance, lagging 21.3
seconds behind Hanevold's winning time of 55:00.6.
</P>
<P>
Gross leads the World Cup standings with 145 points over
Frenchman Raphael Poiree's 142. 
</P>
</TEXT>
