<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Health Services Project in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 15 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
approved a 30 million U.S. dollar loan for Dominican Republic's
provincial health services project.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be used to finance the first World Bank-backed
health care project in the republic, which is one of the most
densely populated countries in Latin America and the Caribbean,
whose health care indicators compare unfavorably with countries of
similar per capita income.
</P>
<P>
With a total cost of 42 million dollars, the project will help
decentralize the country's health care system by transferring
resources and responsibilities from the national government to the
provincial governments and organizations within a framework that
facilitates the integration of public and private providers to
improve access to, as well as efficiency of health services.
</P>
</TEXT>
