<HEADLINE> World Bank Backs Indian Power Sector Restructuring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 15 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
approved a 60 million U.S. dollar loan to help India's power
sector restructuring project.
</P>
<P>
The project will support the first phase of the Haryana Power
Sector Restructuring and Development Program. The program is aimed
to ensure that by the year 2007 the power requirements for the
State's economic growth and its population are met, and that
consumers are provided with reliable and cost-effective
electricity services.
</P>
<P>
The project is designed to back the reform process by
establishing a new legal, regulatory, institutional framework,
initiating the privatization of the distribution business and
removing the most critical bottlenecks of the power system.
