<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves 362 Million U.S. Dollar Credits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 15 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
approved two credits totaling 362.2 million U.S. dollars
equivalent for projects in Ethiopia and Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
First credit of 309.2 million dollars will be utilized for
Ethiopia's road sector development program support project. This
project will restore Ethiopia's road network, develop
institutional capacity of the road agencies, and provide economic
opportunities for the rural population through job creation and
the development of appropriate and affordable means of transport
and services.
</P>
<P>
Another credit of 53 million dollars equivalent is earmarked
for Eritrea's human resources development project.
</P>
<P>
The project will improve the capacity of Government
institutions in a sustainable fashion by resolving the major
problems posed by the acute shortage of skilled and professional
manpower.
</P>
<P>
The credits will be channeled through the International
Development Association (IDA), the World Bank's concessionary
lending arm for developing countries. 
